# The three mount types

Differ in **where bytes live** + **whose lifecycle** governs them.

| Type | Lives | Lifecycle | Best for |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Volume** | Docker area | own; `volume rm` | persistent **app data** |
| **Bind** | any host path | the host path's | **local dev**, config |
| **`tmpfs`** | host RAM | container only | secrets, fast scratch |

## The rule

> **Volume by default. Bind when you need a host path. `tmpfs` when it must never hit disk.**

## Why volume by default

A volume is a **first-class object** — name it, `inspect`, back up, move — decoupled from any container. A bind ties you to an exact host path (breaks on a teammate's box); `tmpfs` vanishes on stop.

Next: named/anonymous volumes → binds → `tmpfs`, then spelling, sharing, backup.
